This article is about an executive order issued by President Barack Obama on May 21, 2012, regarding the order of succession within the Office of Management and Budget. The order outlines the individuals who would act as and perform the functions and duties of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget in case both the Director and Deputy Director are unable to fulfill their roles. It lists the order of succession for various positions within the office. The executive order also includes exceptions and revokes a previous executive order related to the order of succession. It states that the order does not create any enforceable rights or benefits against the United States or any other party.